# Email Accounts Configuration
# Copy this file to .env.email and fill in your credentials.
# DO NOT commit this file to git or share with anyone.

# List your account names (comma-separated)
ACCOUNTS=work

# --- Account: work ---
# Provider: gmail or outlook
work_PROVIDER=gmail
work_USER=your.email@gmail.com
work_PASSWORD=xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx

# --- How to get your App Password ---
#
# IMPORTANT: App Password is NOT your login password.
# It's a separate 16-character password specifically for third-party apps.
#
# Gmail / Google Workspace:
#   Prerequisites:
#     - 2FA (two-step verification) must be enabled on your Google account
#     - IMAP must be enabled: Gmail Settings > See all settings > Forwarding and POP/IMAP > Enable IMAP
#       (Most accounts have this on by default, but some Google Workspace admins disable it)
#   Steps:
#     1. Go to https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
#     2. Select app: "Mail", Select device: "Other" (enter "Claude Email")
#     3. Click "Generate"
#     4. Copy the 16-character password (spaces don't matter)
#
# Outlook / Microsoft 365:
#   Personal Outlook account (outlook.com / hotmail.com):
#     1. Go to https://account.live.com/proofs/AppPassword
#     2. Create a new App Password
#     3. Copy the password here
#
#   Corporate M365 account (your.name@company.com):
#     Your IT department may need to:
#     - Enable IMAP access for your account (Exchange Admin Center > Mailbox > Mailbox features > IMAP)
#     - Enable App Passwords (Azure AD > Security > MFA > Additional cloud-based MFA settings)
#     If App Passwords are disabled by policy, ask IT for an alternative IMAP access method.
#     Some orgs require OAuth2 — in that case, set work_HOST and work_PORT manually.

# --- Multiple accounts (optional) ---
# ACCOUNTS=work,personal
#
# personal_PROVIDER=outlook
# personal_USER=your.email@company.com
# personal_PASSWORD=xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx

# --- Advanced: custom IMAP settings (optional) ---
# Override host, port, or drafts folder if auto-detection doesn't work:
# work_HOST=imap.custom-server.com
# work_PORT=993
# work_DRAFTS_FOLDER=Drafts
#
# Security mode (auto-detected from port if not set):
#   ssl       — IMAP4_SSL, for port 993 (default for Gmail/Outlook)
#   starttls  — IMAP4 + STARTTLS, for port 143 (common for self-hosted servers)
#   none      — plain IMAP, no encryption (not recommended)
# work_SECURITY=starttls
#
# To find your drafts folder name, run:
#   python3 email_ops.py list_folders work
